    <div class="article" id="titleUserReviewsTeaser">
        <h2>User Reviews</h2>
        <div class="user-comments">
                    <div class="tinystarbar" title="10/10">
                        <div style="width: 100px;">&nbsp;</div>
                    </div>
                <span itemprop="review" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">  
                    <strong itemprop="name">Vishwaroopam, a technical masterpiece, competing against any world class making</strong>
                    <span itemprop="reviewRating" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Rating">
                        <meta itemprop="worstRating" content = "1" />
                        <meta itemprop="ratingValue" content="10" />
                        <meta itemprop="bestRating" content="10" />
                    </span>
                    <div class="comment-meta">
                        27 January 2013 | by <a href="/user/ur40373166/?ref_=tt_urv"
><span itemprop="author">Madhu Chakravarthi</span></a>
                        <meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2013-01-27" />
                              (Chicago, IL)
                        &ndash; <a href="/user/ur40373166/comments?ref_=tt_urv"
>See all my reviews</a>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p itemprop="reviewBody">Vishwaroopam - Technically ... the best Indian movie I&#x27;ve seen so far...be it content, cinematography, audiography, art and editing. Multi-layered screenplay ... director Kamal scores here.... the movie is definitely a little slow when you&#x27;re watching especially the afghan episode in first half ... once the movie is over and when it sinks in after a couple of hours .. you&#x27;d think of watching again for the making. The songs gelled really well with the movie however the bgm was very disappointing that most of the scenes were blank and brought down the pace of the movie.<br /><br />Kamal Haasan&#x27;s transformation was stunning and unexpected. 10/10 as an actor. Rahul bose&#x27;s performance was noteworthy. Remaining actors Pooja Kumar, Andrea and Shekar Kapoor did a decent job. Very good casting.<br /><br />On the controversy... there is nothing shown against Islam or Muslims.. in fact there were a couple of jokes about Hindus/Brahmins. The movie has attempted to show jihads as they are .. nothing that we&#x27;ve never seen in TV/Internet ... There is just a 1 minute scene in the whole movie that shows Indian Muslims in a great way and the amount of pain caused to Muslims and their families by these terrorists and the way the world treats Muslims (including Indian Hindus). This one scene forms the core... making it the most Muslim friendly movie ever. The only reason for you to get offended would be that you&#x27;re a jihad and you don&#x27;t like a movie that shows you who you are and what you have done.<br /><br />$15 not down the drain.. in fact I&#x27;m thinking of night show tonight ... something I&#x27;ve never done in my life!</p>
                    </div>
                </span>
                <hr />
                <div class="yn" id="ynd_2743927">
                    139 of 164 people found this review helpful.&nbsp;
